The paper discusses interpretability of AI models, which is a topic that falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions distributional semantics (cs.CL), fuzzy logic (cs.LG), and human-centered interpretability solutions (cs.SI), which are all sub-fields of AI that are relevant to the topic of interpretability. Additionally, the paper discusses how different approaches affect the final users, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
